---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | gsheetbase.com"
  description="Privacy policy for gsheetbase.com"
>
  <main class="w-full flex flex-col items-center">
    <article class="w-full max-w-[800px] px-6 py-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tighter mb-4">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8">
        Last updated: February 7, 2026
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            1. Introduction
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            GsheetBase (&quot;GsheetBase&quot;, &quot;we&quot;, &quot;our&quot;,
            or &quot;us&quot;) provides a web application that connects to your
            Google Account so you can view and sync data from your Google Sheets
            within our product.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and share
            information, including information obtained through Google APIs. By
            using GsheetBase, you agree to the practices described in this
            Privacy Policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            2. Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may collect, use, store, and transfer different kinds of
            information about you when you use GsheetBase:
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            2.1 Account and Contact Information
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Name (if provided)</li>
            <li>Workspace or organization name (if provided)</li>
            <li>
              Authentication identifiers and access logs (such as sign-in
              timestamps, IP address, and browser information)
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            2.2 Billing and Subscription Information
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Payment and billing details (processed via our payment providers)
            </li>
            <li>Subscription plan, invoices, and transaction history</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            2.3 Usage Information
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Actions taken in the application (for example, connecting a sheet
              or configuring syncs)
            </li>
            <li>Device, browser, and technical log data</li>
            <li>Aggregated analytics about feature usage</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            2.4 Google User Data (via Google APIs)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            When you connect your Google account and authorize GsheetBase, we
            access specific Google user data under the following scopes:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              <code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets.readonly</code> (required
              for read-only access)
            </li>
            <li>
              <code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets</code> (optional,
              only if you enable write/sync features)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Depending on how you use GsheetBase, we may access:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Google Sheets metadata: spreadsheet IDs, titles, sheet names, and
              structure (such as columns and ranges)
            </li>
            <li>
              Google Sheets content: cell values, formulas, and other data
              contained in your spreadsheets
            </li>
            <li>
              Basic profile information from Google (such as your email address)
              used for identifying your account and permissions
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We do not access your Gmail, Google Drive files other than the
            specific spreadsheets you connect, or any other Google data outside
            the granted scopes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            3. Why We Access Google User Data
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We access Google Sheets data solely to provide and improve the
            GsheetBase service, including:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Displaying your Google Sheets data inside the GsheetBase interface
            </li>
            <li>
              Enabling you to configure and run syncs between Google Sheets and
              other parts of our application
            </li>
            <li>
              Performing operations you explicitly request (such as reading
              ranges or writing updates if you enabled write access)
            </li>
            <li>
              Maintaining and troubleshooting your connections and
              configurations
            </li>
            <li>
              Ensuring security, abuse prevention, and reliability of the
              integration
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We do not access Google user data for advertising, selling data, or
            building unrelated products.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            4. How We Use Google User Data
          </h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            4.1 Core Product Functionality
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              To read Google Sheets data you select and display it in our
              dashboards, tables, or views
            </li>
            <li>
              To process and transform that data (for example, filters,
              calculations, mappings) as configured by you
            </li>
            <li>
              If you enable write access, to update your spreadsheets with
              changes or sync results that you explicitly configure
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            4.2 Account Management and Support
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              To associate connected spreadsheets with your GsheetBase account
            </li>
            <li>
              To provide customer support and investigate reported issues (which
              may involve limited, logged access to specific data as necessary
              to resolve a support ticket and only with appropriate safeguards)
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            4.3 Security, Abuse Prevention, and Compliance
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300"
          >
            <li>To secure access tokens and verify authorization</li>
            <li>
              To detect and prevent misuse, fraud, or abuse of the integration
            </li>
            <li>
              To comply with applicable law, regulation, and legal process where
              required
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            We do not use Google user data to create or augment profiles for
            advertising, or to train generalized AI or machine learning models.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            5. Where and How We Store Google User Data
          </h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            5.1 Storage Locations
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We store data on secure cloud infrastructure operated by reputable
            third-party providers located in data centers in regions such as the
            United States or other jurisdictions with adequate protections.
            Access tokens and refresh tokens are stored in encrypted form and
            are used only by our servers to access the Google APIs on your
            behalf.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            5.2 Data Stored by Default
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Identifiers and metadata for spreadsheets you connect (such as
              spreadsheet IDs, names, and sheet structure)
            </li>
            <li>
              Configuration data (for example, which sheets, ranges, and columns
              are mapped, and your sync rules and schedules)
            </li>
            <li>
              Logs of API requests and system events for security, debugging,
              and compliance
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            5.3 Optional Storage of Sheet Content
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            In many cases, we read your Google Sheets data on demand and process
            it transiently in memory. If you enable certain features (such as
            background sync, caching, or integrations that require persistent
            storage), we may store copies of relevant rows, columns, or derived
            data in our databases to provide those features efficiently. In all
            cases, stored content is treated as confidential and is protected
            using industry-standard security measures, including encryption in
            transit, access controls, and monitoring.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            6. Data Retention
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We retain information according to the following principles:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              <strong>Account data:</strong> retained for as long as your account
              is active and for a reasonable period thereafter as necessary for billing,
              legal, or operational purposes.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Google user data (content and metadata):</strong> retained only
              for as long as necessary to provide the features you have enabled (such
              as sync jobs and configuration) and to maintain service integrity and
              security.
            </li>
            <li>
              When you disconnect your Google account from GsheetBase or delete
              specific integrations, we will revoke or delete related access
              tokens and remove or anonymize associated configuration and stored
              content from our systems within a reasonable period, subject to
              backups and legal obligations.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Backups:</strong> data may remain in system backups for a limited
              time before being purged on a scheduled basis.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You may request deletion of your account and associated data by
            contacting us as described in the &quot;Contact Us&quot; section
            below.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            7. Data Sharing and Third Parties
          </h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            7.1 No Selling or Sharing of Google User Data
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We do not sell, rent, or lease your Google user data or other
            personal information to third parties. We do not share Google user
            data with third parties for their own independent marketing or
            advertising purposes.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            7.2 Service Providers
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may share limited data with third-party service providers who
            perform services on our behalf, such as:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>Cloud hosting and infrastructure</li>
            <li>Database and logging services</li>
            <li>Payment processing</li>
            <li>Customer support tools</li>
            <li>Analytics and monitoring</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            These providers may process data only under our instructions, for
            the sole purpose of providing their services to us, and are bound by
            confidentiality and data protection obligations at least as
            protective as those in this Privacy Policy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">
            7.3 Legal and Safety Requirements
          </h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may disclose information if we reasonably believe it is necessary
            to:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              Comply with an applicable law, regulation, legal process, or
              enforceable governmental request
            </li>
            <li>
              Enforce our Terms of Service or protect the security and integrity
              of GsheetBase
            </li>
            <li>
              Protect the rights, property, or safety of GsheetBase, our users,
              or the public
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Any such disclosure of Google user data will be strictly limited and
            consistent with the Google API Services User Data Policy, including
            its Limited Use requirements.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            8. How You Can Revoke Google Access
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You remain in control of your Google account and Google user data at
            all times. You can revoke GsheetBase’s access to your Google account
            in the following ways:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              From your Google Account: visit your Google Account permissions at
              <a
                href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions"
                class="text-primary hover:underline"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                https://myaccount.google.com/permissions
              </a>
              , find &quot;GsheetBase&quot; in the list of connected apps, and remove
              its access.
            </li>
            <li>
              From within GsheetBase: use the account or integrations settings
              in our app to disconnect your Google account and remove configured
              connections.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Once access is revoked, GsheetBase will no longer be able to call
            Google APIs on your behalf. We will delete or anonymize stored
            Google user data associated with the revoked connection within a
            reasonable timeframe, subject to backups and legal requirements as
            described in the &quot;Data Retention&quot; section above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            9. Compliance with Google API Services User Data Policy and Limited
            Use
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Our use of information received from Google APIs, including data
            obtained via the scopes
            <code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets.readonly</code> and
            <code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets</code>, adheres
            to the Google API Services User Data Policy, including its Limited
            Use requirements.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>
              We only access, use, and store Google user data that is necessary
              to provide and improve the GsheetBase features you choose to use.
            </li>
            <li>
              We do not use Google user data for advertising, targeting ads, or
              creating advertising profiles.
            </li>
            <li>
              We do not sell or transfer Google user data to third parties,
              except as necessary to provide or secure our service, comply with
              applicable law, or as part of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale
              where the data protections will remain at least as protective.
            </li>
            <li>
              We do not use Google user data to develop, improve, or train
              generalized AI or machine learning models.
            </li>
            <li>
              Human access to Google user data is strictly limited, logged, and
              only allowed when necessary for security, support, legal
              compliance, or service reliability, and always under obligations
              of confidentiality.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">10. Security</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We use technical and organizational measures designed to protect
            your information, including Google user data, from unauthorized
            access, loss, misuse, or alteration, such as:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>Encryption in transit (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
            <li>
              Encrypted storage for sensitive credentials (such as OAuth tokens)
            </li>
            <li>
              Access controls restricting internal access to data on a
              need-to-know basis
            </li>
            <li>
              Logging and monitoring of access and relevant system activities
            </li>
            <li>
              Regular updates and security reviews of our infrastructure and
              code
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            No method of transmission or storage is completely secure. While we
            strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute
            security.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            11. Children&apos;s Privacy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            GsheetBase is not directed to children under 16, and we do not
            knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If we
            discover that we have collected information from a child under 16
            without appropriate consent, we will delete that information as soon
            as reasonably possible.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            12. Your Rights and Choices
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights with respect to
            your personal information, such as:
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4"
          >
            <li>Accessing the information we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correcting or updating inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Requesting deletion of your personal information</li>
            <li>Objecting to or restricting certain processing</li>
            <li>Exporting your data in a portable format (where applicable)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You can exercise these rights by contacting us using the details
            below. We may need to verify your identity before responding. You
            can also control and revoke GsheetBase’s access to your Google
            account at any time as described in the &quot;How You Can Revoke
            Google Access&quot; section above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
            13. Changes to This Privacy Policy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make
            material changes, we will notify you by posting the updated policy
            on our website, providing a notice within the GsheetBase
            application, and/or sending an email to the address associated with
            your account.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Your continued use of GsheetBase after any update constitutes your
            acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">14. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, our use of Google
            user data, or your privacy rights, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-1">
            GsheetBase
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-1">
            Email:
            <a
              href="mailto:support@gsheetbase.com"
              class="text-primary hover:underline">support@gsheetbase.com</a
            >
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Website:
            <a
              href="https://www.gsheetbase.com"
              class="text-primary hover:underline"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.gsheetbase.com</a
            >
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
